# Reference: RODECaster Duo virtual sinks generated by rodecaster-duo-pipewire AUR package
#
# Purpose:    Documents what the rodecaster-duo-pipewire AUR package creates automatically.
#             This file is for reference only — it shows the System and Chat virtual sinks
#             that route audio to RODECaster Duo channels.
#
# DO NOT deploy manually — the AUR package generates these configs.
# Verify the sinks are present with: wpctl status | grep rcp_duo
#
# To install the package and activate Pro Audio mode:
#   yay -S rodecaster-duo-pipewire
#   rodecaster-duo-set-pro-audio      # connect device first
#   rodecaster-duo-pipewire-install
#   systemctl --user restart pipewire pipewire-pulse wireplumber
#
# Channel mapping:
#   rcp_duo_system_in  — System channel  → RODECaster AUX0/AUX1 pair (main program mix)
#   rcp_duo_chat_in    — Chat channel    → RODECaster FL/FR pair   (voice chat, Discord)
#
# Per-app routing:
#   Steam, games, browser, Spotify → System (rcp_duo_system_in) — default sink
#   Discord, OBS mic monitor       → Chat   (rcp_duo_chat_in)
#
# NOTE: Only System and Chat channels are used. Game and Music channels are omitted —
# they did not work reliably with the RODECaster Duo's channel mapping.
#
# --- AUR-generated config (representative — actual file written by AUR package) ---

# Virtual sink: RODECaster System channel (AUX0/AUX1 pair)
# node.name = rcp_duo_system_in
# media.class = Audio/Sink
# Routes to RODECaster Duo System channel AUX input pair

# Virtual sink: RODECaster Chat channel (FL/FR pair)
# node.name = rcp_duo_chat_in
# media.class = Audio/Sink
# Routes to RODECaster Duo Chat channel main input pair
